tory and navigational sections are mostly structural, while \"作成手順\" with its subsections contains the actual substantive content. However, I'm noticing that \"作成内容\" under the h3 level includes a table with JSP file names and descriptions—that's meaningful information I need to verify is being captured properly in the consolidated structure. Looking at the knowledge file more carefully, I see the relationship between W11AC0201.jsp and W11AC0202.jsp is documented, though the specific functionality description for W11AC0201.jsp gets lost in the table structure. I'm also noticing that s2 contains an RST reference syntax that won't render properly in this context, and there's a discrepancy where \"自動的に\" appears to be added in the fabricated version when the source only mentions content restoration without that qualifier. I'm noticing that the word \"自動的に\" (automatically) was added to the knowledge file but doesn't appear in the original source material. The source says the input content will be restored if you simply transition back to the previous screen, but the knowledge file adds the qualifier that this happens automatically, which is a subtle fabrication I should flag. The S9 warning about section count seems less significant than I initially thought—the source includes navigational scaffolding sections that don't contain substantive content, so the knowledge file's focus on the two main sections (implementation and input restoration) captures the essential information. The \"画面イメージ\" section does describe button interactions, but it's mostly introductory framing rather than critical context.\n\nLooking at my findings, the key issue is the fabrication in s2 where \"自動的に\" was added—that's marked as critical severity under V2, even though it's a minor semantic addition. I'm also verifying V3 for section length and ID sequencing: both s1 and s2 exceed 50 characters and follow the proper sequential format, so no problems there. For V4 hints in s1, I'm seeing references to form handling, submission, URI attributes, HTML forms, screen transitions, and the JSP file path—all of which align with the content. Looking back at the source text more carefully, I can see the knowledge base added \"自動的に\" (automatically) where the original only says the input content will be restored—it doesn't explicitly state it happens automatically. This is indeed a fabrication, and while it's a subtle addition that doesn't drastically change the meaning, the schema classifies all fabrications as critical severity, so I'll report it that way.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17827,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":17827,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"50b27553-432f-4558-903e-930c9e9121ae","uuid":"8ecfbd66-9459-484e-bfca-86a8d57a78b6"}
